\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 3. Target End State\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 MorphIQ will be a production-ready document scanning and compliance platform for five letting agencies, deployed on a Hetzner VPS, with a secure admin model, a documented local operations mode, and a controlled onboarding process for new agencies.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 3.1 Business and operational target\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Each agency has its own login area, its own users, and data isolation that prevents cross-client access.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Super-admin users can view and manage all agencies from a controlled admin layer.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab The system supports scanning, OCR, AI extraction, human review, sync to portal, compliance reporting, property packs, and agency-level reporting.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab The system has documented onboarding, backups, recovery, support, monitoring, and release management.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 3.2 Technical target\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Production application runs on Hetzner behind a reverse proxy with HTTPS.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Production database is organized by client and designed to prevent client data crossover.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Authentication, authorization, audit logging, password handling, and session security are fully implemented and tested.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Critical flows are covered by automated and manual test suites.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Deployment, rollback, backup, restore, and environment configuration are documented and repeatable.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 4. Required Architecture Decisions\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 Because the target is five agencies with strict separation and reliable administration, the architecture must be deliberately defined before feature finishing begins. The recommended architecture is below.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 4.1 Recommended production model\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Use one production MorphIQ application deployment on Hetzner.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Use one central application codebase and one central admin control plane.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Use one database server technology that supports production operations cleanly. Recommended: PostgreSQL for production, while keeping SQLite only for local development or transitional tooling if needed.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Implement client isolation at the application, query, service, and admin layers using a mandatory client or tenant boundary model.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Every agency user belongs to exactly one client tenant. Every business record belongs to exactly one client tenant. Every agency-facing query must be automatically constrained to that tenant.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Super-admin users can switch client context, but every admin action must still be logged with actor, timestamp, client, route, and action type.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 4.2 Why this is the recommended model\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 The current project already behaves like a client-oriented multi-tenant application, even though some parts of the data model and route protection still need tightening. Running five separate code deployments and five separate operational stacks would make support, release management, and upgrades heavier. A single secured platform with strict tenant isolation and role-based access is the most practical route for finishing the product cleanly and operating it on your Hetzner VPS.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 4.3 Non-negotiable security rules\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab No agency user can query, download, mutate, export, or infer another agency's data.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab All document, property, compliance, pack, report, and activity endpoints must enforce tenant scope server-side.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab All admin-only actions must require explicit admin role checks.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab All PDF and file-serving routes must be authenticated and tenant-checked.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Passwords must be stored only as secure hashes and managed by a proper reset flow.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab All secrets must be environment-managed and never hardcoded.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 5. Master Workstreams\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 The rest of the project should be executed as eight workstreams. Each workstream must be completed to exit criteria before the next go-live milestone.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream A: architecture and deployment foundation.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream B: data model and tenant isolation.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream C: authentication, authorization, and security.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream D: core portal completion.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream E: pipeline and operational workflow.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream F: testing and quality assurance.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream G: production readiness and observability.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Workstream H: client onboarding and commercial operations.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 6. Phased Delivery Roadmap\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 0: Freeze scope, create the delivery board, classify every item as blocker, must-have, should-have, or post-launch, and lock staging and production success criteria.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 1: Secure the platform by fixing auth gaps, tenant gaps, public file routes, destructive route permissions, debug logging, and startup validation.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 2: Normalize the data and user model by finalizing tenant ownership rules, user roles, password reset flow, migrations, and seed data.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 3: Finish the portal and operator workflow by completing active pages, removing stale pages, and validating user journeys.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 4: Productionize the pipeline by validating scan, OCR, AI prefill, review, sync, retries, duplicate handling, and failure paths.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 5: Build the hosting, deployment, and support layer on Hetzner with reverse proxy, HTTPS, process management, backups, restore tests, and monitoring.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 6: Run internal UAT and one controlled pilot onboarding before wider launch.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Phase 7: Launch the five-agency offering only after all quality gates are signed off.\par
