\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 8. Client Isolation Model\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 The platform must treat client isolation as a core invariant, not a UI preference. The following model must be implemented and tested before any agency launch.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Each agency has one client record and one or more agency users attached only to that client.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Every property belongs to one client.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Every document belongs to one client and, where applicable, one property.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Every compliance record and pack belongs to one client, directly or indirectly through owned records.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Every agency-facing query must derive its scope from authenticated user context, never from trusting user-supplied IDs alone.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Admins can view all clients, but every admin view must still be explicit about which client is being viewed or changed.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Audit logs must record actor, role, client context, entity type, entity ID, timestamp, and action.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 9. User and Login Model\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Super admin: full cross-client access, client switching, user creation, destructive maintenance, exports, and audit review.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Internal admin: internal support and operations role with controlled permissions defined by policy.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Client manager: can manage only their agency's data and users according to granted permissions.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Reviewer: can verify documents and review compliance for their agency only if this role is required operationally.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Read-only user: can view agency information but cannot mutate records if this role is needed for some agencies.\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 Each of the five agencies should have at minimum one primary client manager account and one backup admin-approved contact account. You should also maintain at least one emergency internal super-admin account outside normal daily use.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 10. Five-Agency Launch Preparation Checklist\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Create the five client records with final production names and slugs.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Create initial client manager users for each agency.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Create password reset invitations or first-login setup process.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Load or import each agency's property portfolio.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Validate agency-specific branding or labels if required.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Validate each agency can log in and only see its own properties, documents, packs, activity, and reports.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Validate admin can switch into each agency context and back out safely.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Validate one full document lifecycle for each agency using representative sample documents.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Validate export outputs and downloads for each agency.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Provide each agency with login instructions, support contact, and issue reporting process.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 11. Hetzner VPS Production Build Checklist\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Provision VPS with stable OS, firewall, deployment user, SSH key access, and patching policy.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Install Python runtime, database engine, reverse proxy, SSL tooling, and process manager.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Create application directory structure for releases, shared config, logs, backups, and uploads.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Deploy application code to staging first, then production.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Configure environment variables and secret files securely.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Configure reverse proxy routes for portal and API endpoints.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Enable HTTPS and redirect HTTP to HTTPS.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Configure service auto-start on reboot.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Configure scheduled backups for database and critical documents.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Run restore test from backup before onboarding any customer.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Configure monitoring alerts for downtime, disk space, certificate expiry, and backup failures.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 12. Local Operations Checklist\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Document exact Windows setup for scanning operators.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Document how local scan batches are created, named, processed, reviewed, and synced.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Ensure local setup does not depend on outdated hardcoded root paths.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Create quick health-check script for local operators.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Create issue escalation guide for OCR failure, AI failure, sync failure, and portal access failure.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 13. Quality Gates\b0\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 13.1 Security gate\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab No unauthenticated access to protected data or files.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab No cross-tenant access path found in tests.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Admin-only actions require admin role and are audited.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 13.2 Data gate\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Migrations run cleanly on fresh and existing environments.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Backups and restores are proven.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Sample onboarding and data imports run without manual database surgery.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 13.3 Functional gate\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Core portal flows pass: login, property browsing, document viewing, PDF viewing, packs, compliance, reports, settings, activity, AI chat.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Core pipeline flows pass: scan, OCR, AI prefill, review, sync, portal visibility.\par
\pard\sa120\b\fs24 13.4 Operational gate\b0\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Deployment is repeatable.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Rollback is documented and tested.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Monitoring and alerts are live.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Runbooks exist and are usable by someone other than the original builder.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 14. Definition Of Done\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 MorphIQ should only be considered finished for launch when all of the following are true.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab A new client can be onboarded without code edits or database hand-fixing.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Each agency user can access only their own tenant data.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Admins can manage all agencies safely through audited controls.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab The scan-to-portal workflow works end to end for all supported document types.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab The portal pages are complete, current, and free from placeholder content or stale duplicates.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab All production secrets, backups, monitoring, deployment, and restore procedures are implemented.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Automated tests and manual UAT pass on staging.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab Pilot onboarding succeeds for at least one real or realistic client account before full rollout.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab You can confidently invite a letting agency customer into the platform without warning them about unfinished features or manual workarounds.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 15. Immediate Next Actions\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 Use these as the next execution sequence once you reopen development.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 1. Convert this document into backlog tickets grouped by the eight workstreams.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 2. Start with the security and tenant-isolation fixes found in the audit.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 3. Decide and lock the production database strategy for Hetzner.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 4. Build staging and production infrastructure before late-stage feature work expands further.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 5. Run one full hardening pass on auth, downloads, destructive routes, and admin controls.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 6. Finish the portal gaps and remove stale assets or templates.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 7. Stabilize and test the full scan-to-portal pipeline against representative agency data.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 8. Build backups, monitoring, deployment, and restore tests.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 9. Prepare one pilot agency onboarding pack and execute it end to end.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa80\fs22 \'95\tab 10. Only after pilot sign-off, onboard the remaining agencies.\par
\pard\sa160\b\f1\fs28 16. Closing Assessment\b0\par
\pard\sa120\fs22 MorphIQ is already far enough along that this should be treated as a finishing and productionization project, not a greenfield rebuild. The platform has genuine assets in place: a portal, authentication base, pipeline components, a working client-oriented data model, and live business data patterns. The correct path now is disciplined hardening, completion, cleanup, hosting, and operations design. If this plan is executed in order, you will end with a platform that is not only feature-complete, but safe to run for real agencies on your Hetzner VPS and practical to support day to day.\par
